1 3. HAS BEEN PUBLISHING OR BROADCASTING NEWS FOR
2 AT LEAST 1 YEAR; AND
3 4. CARRIES A MEDIA LIABILITY INSURANCE POLICY AT
4 ALL TIMES DURING A TAXABLE YEAR.
5 (II) “LOCAL NEWSROOM” DOES NOT INCLUDE A NEWS
6 ORGANIZATION THAT IS OWNED OR FUNDED BY A POLITICAL ADVOCACY GROUP,
7 INCLUDING AN ORGANIZATION AUTHORIZED TO ENGAGE IN POLITICAL ACTIVITY
8 UNDER § 501(C) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE.
9 (3) “LOCAL NEWSROOM EMPLOYEE” MEANS AN EMPLOYEE ENGAGED
10 OR ASSISTING IN THE GATHERING, PREPARING, COLLECTING, WRITING,
11 RECORDING, DIRECTING THE RECORDING, PRODUCING, EDITING,
12 PHOTOGRAPHING, REPORTING, PRESENTING, OR PUBLISHING OF LOCAL
13 COMMUNITY NEWS IN THE STATE FOR DISSEMINATION TO THE LOCAL COMMUNITY.
14 (B) (1) SUBJECT TO THE LIMITATIONS OF THIS SUBSECTION, FOR EACH
15 TAXABLE YEAR A LOCAL NEWSROOM MAY CLAIM A CREDIT AGAINST THE STATE
16 INCOME TAX FOR EACH FULL–TIME LOCAL NEWSROOM EMPLOYEE EMPLOYED BY
17 THE LOCAL NEWSROOM IN AN AMOUNT UP TO:
18 (I) $25,000 OF THE WAGES PAID TO EACH FULL–TIME LOCAL
19 NEWSROOM EMPLOYEE FOR THE FIRST TAXABLE YEAR THAT THE LOCAL NEWSROOM
20 CLAIMS THE CREDIT FOR THAT LOCAL NEWSROOM EMPLOYEE; AND
21 (II) $15,000 OF THE WAGES PAID TO EACH FULL–TIME LOCAL
22 NEWSROOM EMPLOYEE FOR EACH SUBSEQUENT TAXABLE YEAR THAT THE LOCAL
23 NEWSROOM CLAIMS THE CREDIT FOR THAT LOCAL NEWSROOM EMPLOYEE.
24 (2) A LOCAL NEWSROOM MAY NOT CLAIM A TAX CREDIT UNDER THIS
25 SECTION FOR MORE THAN 5 TAXABLE YEARS FOR ANY INDIVIDUAL LOCAL
26 NEWSROOM EMPLOYEE.
27 (C) IF THE TAX CREDIT ALLOWED UNDER THIS SECTION IN ANY TAXABLE
28 YEAR EXCEEDS THE TOTAL TAX OTHERWISE PAYABLE BY THE LOCAL NEWSROOM
29 FOR THAT TAXABLE YEAR, THE LOCAL NEWSROOM MAY CLAIM A REFUND IN THE
30 AMOUNT OF THE EXCESS.
31 (D) A LOCAL NEWSROOM THAT IS EXEMPT FROM TAXATION UNDER § 501(C)
32 OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE MAY APPLY THE CREDIT UNDER THIS SECTION

